menu "breadboard: bb_sink_http"

config BB_SINK_HTTP_RESP_BUF_BYTES
    int "Response buffer size for HTTP publish (bytes)"
    default 256
    help
        Size of the stack-allocated response buffer used by bb_sink_http on
        each publish call. AWS IoT Core returns a minimal JSON body on
        success; 256 bytes is sufficient. Increase if your endpoint returns
        larger responses.

config BB_SINK_HTTP_MAX_CONSEC_FAILURES
    int "Consecutive transport failures before session reset"
    default 3
    range 1 20
    help
        When this many consecutive publish transport errors occur on the
        reusable keep-alive session, the session is closed and re-opened on
        the next publish attempt. A lower value recovers faster from server-
        side idle-socket evictions; a higher value tolerates transient blips
        without incurring reconnect overhead. Default 3 matches the prior
        hardcoded value (no behavior change).

config BB_SINK_HTTP_HEADERS_BUF_BYTES
    int "NVS serialization buffer size for configured headers (bytes)"
    default 2596
    range 512 8192
    help
        Size of the buffer used to serialize and read back the configured
        HTTP headers from NVS. The minimum safe value is
        BB_SINK_HTTP_HEADERS_MAX * (BB_SINK_HTTP_HEADER_NAME_MAX +
        BB_SINK_HTTP_HEADER_VALUE_MAX + 4) = 8 * (64 + 256 + 4) = 2592
        bytes. The default (2596) covers the maximum header set with 4 bytes
        of headroom. Increase if you need more headers than the default
        BB_SINK_HTTP_HEADERS_MAX (8).

endmenu
